{
  "text": "I'd like to expand a little on the concept of work. In Newtonian physics, the concept of work is what we call a force which moves through space. It's the product of force and distance as we measure it. I'm assuming that the work of which you speak is a much broader term, including possibly work in consciousness. Am I correct? I am Ra. As we use this term, it is universal in application, intelligent infinity has a rhythm or a flow as of a giant heart, a beginning with the central, a sun, as you would think or conceive of this the presence of the flow inevitable as a tide of a beingness without polarity, without finity, the vast and silent all beating outward, outward, focusing outward and inward until the focuses are complete the intelligence or consciousness of foci have reached a state where there shall we say spiritual nature or mass calls them inward, inward, inward until all is a co allest. This is the rhythm of reality as you spoke.",
